Cut numeric variables into intervals

cutR.Rd

Wrapper for cut() with simplified labels and automatic conversion to factor based on most frequent levels

Usage

cutR(data, vars, seqlist, name.list = list(), name.pattern = NULL, digits = 0)

Arguments

data

dataframe. Works with piping.

vars

Vector of vars which should be cut

seqlist

List of the split patterns for each var. E.g. list("v1" = seq(0,10), "v2" = round(quantile(df %>% pull(age), seq(0,1,0.1)),0))

name.list

Whether the split should overwrite or as a new variable

name.pattern

Optional naming pattern that should automatically be pasted on the end of the variable name.

Value

The inputted dataframe with the cut variables

Examples

redcap_df %>%
  cutR(size, seq(0,100,10)) %>%
  str
